#Suicide risk factors include;

1. Prior suicide attempt(s) or witnessing of suicide
2. Misuse & abuse of alcohol or other drugs
3. Mental illnesses (depression & other mood disorders)
4. Social isolation
5. Chronic disease & disability
6. Poor access to behavioral health care

Early identification, assessment, management & follow-up applies to people who have attempted #suicide or are perceived to be at risk. Previous suicide attempt is one of the most notable risk factors for a future suicide.
